6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to schools; requiring school district
to spend certain percentage of budget on
8 instructional expenditures; mandating annual increase
to comply with requirement; providing for written
9 warning notice for failure to comply; directing
warning notice be posted on district website;
10 requiring increased compensation for failure to
comply for four consecutive years; mandating
11 permanent compensation increase; defining terms;
providing for codification; providing an effective
12 date; and declaring an emergency.
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 5-128.3 of Title 70, unless
18 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. Beginning with the 2025-2026 school year, the board of
20 education of each school district in the state shall spend no less
21 than sixty percent (60%) of its annual budget on instructional
22 expenditures.
23 B. If a school district spends less than sixty percent (60%) of
24 its annual budget on instructional expenditures, it shall increase
Req. No. 12147 Page 1

1 its instructional expenditures by no less than two percent (2%) each
2 year until the amount spent on instructional expenditures reaches
3 sixty percent (60%) of its annual budget.
4 C. If a school district spends less than sixty percent (60%) of
5 its annual budget on instructional expenditures and does not
6 increase its spending as provided in subsection B of this section,
7 the school district shall receive a written warning notice from the
8 State Department of Education. The notice shall also be posted on
9 the website of the school district.
10 D. If a school district spends less than sixty percent (60%) of
11 its annual budget on instructional expenditures and does not
12 increase its spending as provided in subsection B of this section
13 for four (4) consecutive years after receiving the notice provided
14 in subsection C of this section, the school district shall increase
15 compensation for all teachers in the school district by two percent
16 (2%) for each year in that period in which the school district did
17 not increase instructional expenditures by a minimum of two percent
18 (2%). The pay increase required pursuant to this subsection shall
19 be permanent.
20 E. As used in this section:
21 1. "Annual budget" means a plan of financial operations using
22 revenues contributed from local, state, and federal sources but
23 shall not include revenue received from bond sales, the sale of
